# AI Coding Rules

- Respond in Japanese.
- Use sub-agents whenever possible.

## Git Commit Message Format

Required: use Conventional Commits + gitmoji.

### Format

```text
<type>: <emoji> <description>

[optional body]
```

### Type and Emoji Mapping

| Type       | Emoji | Description        |
| ---------- | ----- | ------------------ |
| `feat`     | ✨    | New feature        |
| `fix`      | 🐛    | Bug fix            |
| `docs`     | 📝    | Documentation      |
| `style`    | 💄    | Style / formatting |
| `refactor` | ♻️    | Refactoring        |
| `perf`     | ⚡️    | Performance        |
| `test`     | ✅    | Tests              |
| `build`    | 👷    | Build system       |
| `ci`       | 🎡    | CI/CD              |
| `chore`    | 🔧    | Maintenance        |
| `remove`   | 🔥    | Remove code/files  |
| `deploy`   | 🚀    | Deploy stuff       |

### Examples

```text
feat: ✨ add gitleaks secret scanning
fix: 🐛 resolve rumdl warning
ci: 🎡 bump actions/checkout to v6.0.1
```

## Text Processing

- **MUST**: use `perl` instead of `sed` or `awk` for text processing.
- **MUST**: do not use `cat` to read files.
